# 🎙️ AAWAJ Platform - Implementation Plan

## Overview

**AAWAJ (आवाज)** — "Voice" in Nepali — is an AI-powered civic complaint platform for Kathmandu Valley, Nepal. Citizens report issues (potholes, garbage, water leaks, etc.) by uploading an image + location + text/audio. AI analyzes the complaint, auto-classifies it, and routes it through moderation to a government dashboard.

**Current state**: All frontend HTML files exist but are empty. No backend exists.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **OpenAI API Key**: The AI features (image verification, text classification, priority scoring, audio transcription) require an OpenAI API key. You'll need to provide one after setup. Without it, the system will still work but AI features will use mock/fallback responses.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Project Structure**: The spec mentions the frontend files live in `c:\Project AAWAJ\files\`. I'll create the Django backend in `c:\Project AAWAJ\` as the root, and the frontend HTML files will be served as Django templates from the `files/` folder (renamed to `templates/`). The existing empty `files/*.html` will be populated with full HTML/CSS/JS.

> [!WARNING]
> **Tailwind CSS**: The spec mentions Tailwind. I'll use **Tailwind CDN** for simplicity (no build step). This is fine for development but for production you'd want a build pipeline.

